            Michael Avenatti, lawyer for porn star Stormy Daniels in her suit against President Donald Trump, has been arrested on suspicion of domestic violence, police in Los Angeles say. Celebrity news website TMZ said this followed a physical confrontation between the lawyer and a woman. He denied the claim, and was later released on $50,000 (Â£38,500) bail.The lawyer represents Ms Daniels, who alleges she and President Trump had a brief relationship - a claim he denies.Ms Daniels has sought to free herself from a non-disclosure agreement she signed before the 2016 election.
    
        
